item.title: Getting In The Way Of A Great Song
item.description:
There was a man, a lonely man

Who lived his life

As if it was real

And I don’t know the rest.

The rest, they say, is to be found at the snooker table.

item.title: Birds
item.description:
A blackbird bathing in a pot of water.

A robin sun-bathing.

A sparrow feeding it’s young.

Marvellous sights, indeed.

item.title: Spending The Days Of Your Life
item.description:
